'''Chagas' disease'''

# {{pathology}} A form of [[trypanosomiasis]] prevalent in [[South America]], caused by a parasitic [[trypanosome]]. It is transmitted to [[mammal]]s such as [[human]]s through an [[insect]] bite. Symptoms include fever, [[oedema]], [[cardiomyopathy]], and enlargement of the [[spleen]] and [[lymph node]]s; and can be fatal.